        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-01T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-01T21:00:00-05:00" n="331" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3–247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Butterworth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-02T10:00:00+08:00">March 2, 1947—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 2—2:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>416. Blake at Taipei reports March 2, 10 a.m. that Government removed refugees
                    from Consulate Saturday night just after 10 o’clock without incident and that
                    city appeared calm Sunday morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Butterworth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
